FeedPackage.Description: Managed SDK for the Xbox Music Service.
FeedPackage.ReleaseNotes:
Version 1.7 - Improved localization - Major refactoring - Added support for catalog browsing - Improved sorting and extra query - Added support for Xbox Music subscription discovery - Improved memory usage
Version 1.6.1 - Fixed some minor bugs in the object model - Fix mispelled Lookup method URI
Version 1.6 - Added support for Windows Phone 8.1 - Added support for Silverlight 5 - Code refactoring - Added support for playback streams - Added support for culture specific calls - Added call to get list of genres - Added support for top music
Version 1.5 - Code refactoring - Added support for Spotlight - Added support for New Album releases - General improvements on object model
Version 1.4 - Code refactoring - Added support for continuous search & lookup - Impovements in error handling - Return types refactoring - SearchArtist, SearchTracks, SearchAlbum methods removed - Added support for custom image url
Version 1.3 - Added supporto to .NET 4.0 - Explicitly set country during searches
Version 1.2 - Included automatic token renewal
Version 1.1 - Porting to a PCL - Added error fields serialization
Version 1.0 - Included Artist search - Included Track search - Included Album search - Included Global search

Version 1.7 - Dropped support for legacy platforms - Improved localization - Major refactoring - Added support for catalog browsing - Improved sorting and extra query - Added support for Xbox Music subscription discovery - Improved memory usage
Version 1.6.1 - Fixed some minor bugs in the object model - Fix mispelled Lookup method URI
Version 1.6 - Added support for Windows Phone 8.1 - Added support for Silverlight 5 - Code refactoring - Added support for playback streams - Added support for culture specific calls - Added call to get list of genres - Added support for top music
Version 1.5 - Code refactoring - Added support for Spotlight - Added support for New Album releases - General improvements on object model
Version 1.4 - Code refactoring - Added support for continuous search & lookup - Impovements in error handling - Return types refactoring - SearchArtist, SearchTracks, SearchAlbum methods removed - Added support for custom image url
Version 1.3 - Added supporto to .NET 4.0 - Explicitly set country during searches
Version 1.2 - Included automatic token renewal
Version 1.1 - Porting to a PCL - Added error fields serialization
Version 1.0 - Included Artist search - Included Track search - Included Album search - Included Global search
FeedPackage.Summary: This project is destributed under MS-PL
FeedPackage.Tags: Xbox Music SDK WinRT Windows Phone
FeedPackage.Title: XboxMusicSDK

FeedPackage.Description: A more up-to-date version of https://github.com/mono/guiunit
FeedPackage.ReleaseNotes: Bump to NUnit 3.7.1
FeedPackage.Summary:
This is a small project to compile both a runner and NUnit framework (both based on latest NUnit NuGet package) into a single .exe assembly that can be linked into a test project and used directly to run it.
Like the original GuiUnit, the goal of the runner is to provide integration with a GUI runloop (Gtk, Cocoa, Xwt, ...) so that unit tests that depend on it (for proper async/await operations for instance) can be run correctly.
The verion of this package follows the version of the NUnit dependency it derives from
FeedPackage.Title: Xamarin.GuiUnitNg

FeedPackage.Description: Insights for your Apps.
FeedPackage.ReleaseNotes:
Xamarin Insights 1.6.0 ------------------
The preview release of Xamarin.Insights.
Improve your apps with real-time monitoring. Track crashes and exceptions and understand what is happening with live users.
FeedPackage.Summary: Precise, detailed error reporting.
FeedPackage.Title: Xamarin.Insights

FeedPackage.Description: Insights for your Apps
FeedPackage.ReleaseNotes:
## Features
* New API: ```bool Xamarin.Insights.IsInitialized``` - You can use this to check if insights has been initialized, for example in a library you use across projects that may or may not initialize insights. * New API: ```bool Xamarin.Insights.ForceDataTransmission``` setting this to true will make insights ignore the current network state and attempt communication with the Insights servers. * Android API level < 14 support: This is experimental but does seem to work. If you target API 14 and above but allow your app to run on lower API (tested down to API level 7) we should no longer crash, though you will lose session reporting on lower API levels than 14. We would love to see where this breaks and does not break but for right now, please consider this experimental, it has not been thoroughly tested.
### Fixed Issues:
* #886 - Android, without network change permissions, defaulted to no network connectivity. * #882 - All Platforms, Assembly info reporting, we now report basic assembly information to the server as part of crash reports. * #871 - Android, protection against invalid contexts, if you get the message ```Invalid Android context detected``` in your debug output, you are using insights before your android context is ready to be used. * #862 - iOS, both build number and version number are reported * #852 - All Platforms, New API so you can check if Insights is initialized yet, ```bool Xamarin.Insights.IsInitialized``` will return true if Insights has been initialized * #849 - All Platforms, New API to force data transmission regardless of network state, * #848 - Android, Basic do not crash on Android 2.* support * #831 - Desktop, Garbage collector issue in .net (but not mono) was causing tasks to be dropped and thus usage not being reported to the Insights server, this has been corrected * #830 - Android, NRE client crash on Background change event * #819 - Switch off session sending and reject on endpoint. Old session API was turned off in favour of new event based session tracking. * #908 - Android, crash on resume from background, java NRE when we did not unsubscribe an event listener * #804 - iOS, DivisionByZeroException kills an iOS app
FeedPackage.Summary: Improve your apps with real-time monitoring. Track crashes and exceptions and understand what is happening with live users.
FeedPackage.Title: Xamarin.Insights

FeedPackage.Description: Insights for your Apps
FeedPackage.ReleaseNotes:
# Xamarin Insights client release, version 1.8.0
This release is mostly bug fixes but has some requested changes, most of all, *Unified support!* In addition we increased the precision of all our events which should help the out of order issues some people have been seeing.
aside from minor api overload changes, we have introduced a new call. ```Xamarin.Insights.Save();``` - Please note that this is not intended for regular Insights use, but if you happen to disable Insights automatic exception reporting, you should make sure to call this after all your Insights calls in your own unhandled exception handler.
## Stats for milestone [1.8.0]
### Fixed Issues:
* #1092 - Throw when empty api key is passed to Insights.Initialize() * #1073 - Max Iteration Reached message breaks json * #1028 - mono platform crash in deviceinfo lookup * #1027 - Send Identifier with Trackevents and Reports * #1025 - Use millisecond timestamps for 1.8.0 * #1005 - X-Recurssion-Limit-Reached is not string enclosed * #988 - Android crash in deviceID when app is crashing * #983 - protect against too many open files on android * #981 - Make android stability a bit higher by protecting around registering and unregistering network change recievers * #976 - Android client calls log in plat servcies init which causes a cyclic issue with platform services null checking * #970 - report needs a block variant or switch * #948 - Track/tracktime should provide a dictionaryless api * #947 - TrackTime handles should allow you to add items to the dictionary that we are sending * #896 - locks too early * #807 - Make a Xamarin.Insights component for Rdio and friends * #469 - Support unified api
FeedPackage.Title: Xamarin.Insights

FeedPackage.Description: Do you use the Xceed WPF DataGrid and want to run tests against a virtualizing collection? You've probably noticed that the virtual items don't realize under test. The realization is tied to some voodoo inside the WPF implementation. I've found that by pumping the WPF dispatcher you can make the virtual item realize.
FeedPackage.Summary: Test virtualizing collections by pumping the WPF dispatcher!

FeedPackage.Description:
Xerces-C++ makes it easy to give your application the ability to read and write XML data. A shared library is provided for parsing, generating, manipulating, and validating XML documents using the DOM, SAX, and SAX2 APIs.
Xerces-C++ is faithful to the XML 1.0 recommendation and many associated standards.
The parser provides high performance, modularity, and scalability. Source code, samples and API documentation are provided with the parser. For portability, care has been taken to make minimal use of templates, no RTTI, and minimal use of #ifdefs.
FeedPackage.ReleaseNotes: Dynamic libraries only.
FeedPackage.Summary: Xerces-C++ is a validating XML parser written in a portable subset of C++.

FeedPackage.Description:
This is a .Net wrapper library, written in C#, used to comnunicate with the Xero API.
You can use this library to communicate with the Xero API, without needing any prior knowlege of Xml or OAuth. The library can work in public, private or partner mode.
Note: When using this library, your application should not be set to use .Net 'Client Profile'. This library uses classes that are not part of the client profile.
FeedPackage.Summary: .Net wrapper library for Xero API
FeedPackage.Title: XeroAPI.Net

FeedPackage.Description:
This library allows .net developers to easily upload and download data using the Xero API.
A simple Linq provider has been written to help construct 'where' queries against the API. This allows developers to use the built-in object model to query the data within an organisation.
02-Aug-2011 - Initial version released.
12-Aug-2010 - Updated to allow PDFs of invoices to be downloaded.
